/* $PAGE */
/* $TITLE=Device Profile definitions and selection. */
/* ============================================================================================================================================================= *\
                                                                       Device profile filename.
                                       Device profile file used to select options / configuration parameters for this device.
   NOTE: Although the Device Profile may have the same name than the Device Identifier (also called <Pico Identifier>), they are two different concepts:
         The <Device Profile> is used to control which options / parameters will be used during the build process, whereas the <Device Identifier>
         (or <Pico Identifier>) is a tag (a "name") given to the device internal <Unique ID> (kind of "serial number") and is used primarily at run time
         by the MQTT protocol to identify the source (or target) of a message being received (or transmitted) and / or to determine the recipient 
         (the "target") of a message to be sent.
\* ============================================================================================================================================================= */
#include PROFILE_DEFINE_FILE






